'''单胺氧化酶抑制剂'''（{{lang-en|MAOIs, Monoamine oxidase inhibitor}}）是一类抑制[[单胺氧化酶|单胺氧化酶]]作用的药物。该类药品在[[抑郁症|抑郁症]]的治疗中已有很长的一段历史，相比其他抗抑郁药，该药对[[非典型抑郁障碍|非典型抑郁障碍]]<ref name="李德誠2007">{{cite book |author=李德誠 |title=解讀抑鬱 |url = http://books.google.com/books?id=cceaAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA56 |accessdate=27 March 2014 |date=21 August 2007 |publisher=Sing Tao Publishing |language=zh-tw |ISBN = 978-962-672-600-6|pages=56–}}</ref>的治疗特别地有效<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.psychiatrictimes.com/major-depressive-disorder/atypical-depression-21st-century-diagnostic-and-treatment-issues|title=Atypical Depression in the 21st Century: Diagnostic and Treatment Issues|work=[[Psychiatric_Times|Psychiatric Times]]|accessdate=23 November 2013|author=Cristancho, Mario|archive-date=2013-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202224433/http://www.psychiatrictimes.com/major-depressive-disorder/atypical-depression-21st-century-diagnostic-and-treatment-issues|dead-url=no}}</ref>。MAOIs也被用于[[帕金森氏病|帕金森氏病]]和一些其他疾病的治疗。

由于药物间相互作用饮食不当，该药可能导致严重的[[不良反應_(醫學)|不良反应]]甚至致死， 因此一般作为药物治疗的最后选择，即当其他类型的抗抑郁药（如[[选择性5-羟色胺再摄取抑制剂|选择性5-羟色胺再摄取抑制剂]]和[[三环类抗抑郁药|三环类抗抑郁药]]）<ref name="Lim2011">{{cite book |author=Leslie Lim |title=抑郁症: 被误解的疾病 |url = http://books.google.com/books?id=jj3QMqKzV1cC&pg=PA89|accessdate=27 March 2014|year=2011|publisher=Armour Publishing Pte Ltd|language=zh-cn |ISBN = 978-981-4305-20-4|pages=89–}}</ref>治疗均告无效时才考虑使用MAOIs。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mayoclinic.com/health/depression/DS00175/DSECTION=treatments-and-drugs |title=Mayo Clinic Staff, "Depression (major depression): Treatment and drugs" |accessdate=2014-03-26 |archive-date=2013-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029121006/http://www.mayoclinic.com/health/depression/DS00175/DSECTION=treatments%2Dand%2Ddrugs |dead-url=no }}</ref>近期对MAOIs的研究表明，许多关于该类药品因饮食不当造成的副作用属于误报。该类药品的效用已被证明，但在医药界仍常被误解以至未能得到良好使用。<ref name="Stah">{{cite journal |first2=Stephen M. |last2=Stahl |title=Practical guide for prescribing MAOIs: debunking myths and removing barriers |journal=CNS Spectrums |year=2012 |pages=17, pp 2–10 |doi=10.1017/S109285291200003X |last1=Grady |first1=Meghan M. |volume=17 |url=http://onlinedigeditions.com/display_article.php?id=1047055 |access-date=2014-03-26 |archive-date=2017-07-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707082406/http://onlinedigeditions.com/display_article.php?id=1047055 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> 
近期的研究也对之前的结论提出了质疑，认为不当饮食导致不良反应的严重性值得商榷。<ref>{{cite journal |first1=Beverly J. |last1=McCabe-Sellers |first2=Cathleen G. |last2=Staggs |first3=Margaret L. |last3=Bogle |title=Tyramine in foods and monoamine oxidase inhibitor drugs: A crossroad where medicine, nutrition, pharmacy, and food industry converge |journal=Journal of Food Composition and Analysis 19 (2006) S58–S65 |url=http://naldc.nal.usda.gov/download/7351/PDF |access-date=2014-03-26 |archive-date=2013-04-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130408115558/http://naldc.nal.usda.gov/download/7351/PDF |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==适应症==
新型MAOIs如[[丙炔苯丙胺|丙炔苯丙胺]] (通常用于治疗帕金森氏病) 以及另一种可逆性MAOI[[吗氯贝胺|吗氯贝胺]]是一种更为安全的选择<ref name="pmid2248064"/>，有时已用於一线治疗之中。

MAOIs对[[惊恐障碍|惊恐障碍]]及[[广场恐惧症|广场恐惧症]]、<ref>Buigues J, Vallejo J. Therapeutic response to phenelzine in patients with panic disorder and agoraphobia with panic attacks. Journal of Clinical Psychiatry. 1987;48(2):55–9.</ref> [[社交恐惧症|社交恐惧症]]、<ref>Liebowitz MR, Schneier FR, Campeas R, Hollander E, Hatterer J, Fyer A, et al. Phenelzine vs atenolol in social phobia: A placebo-controlled comparison. Archives of General Psychiatry. 1992;49(4):290–300.</ref><ref>Versiani M, Nardi AE, Mundim FD, Alves AB, Liebowitz MR, Amrein R. Pharmacotherapy of social phobia. A controlled study with moclobemide and phenelzine. BJP [Internet]. 1992 Sep 1 [cited 2013 Oct 4];161(3):353–60. Available from: http://bjp.rcpsych.org/content/161/3/353 {{Wayback|url=http://bjp.rcpsych.org/content/161/3/353 |date=20151120151751 }}</ref><ref>Heimberg RG, Liebowitz MR, Hope DA, et al. Cognitive behavioral group therapy vs phenelzine therapy for social phobia: 12-week outcome. Arch Gen Psychiatry [Internet]. 1998 Dec 1 [cited 2013 Oct 3];55(12):1133–41. Available from: http://dx.doi.org/10.1001/archpsyc.55.12.1133</ref> 非典型抑郁障碍<ref>Jarrett RB, Schaffer M, McIntire D, Witt-Browder A, Kraft D, Risser RC. Treatment of atypical depression with cognitive therapy or phenelzine: A double-blind, placebo-controlled trial. Arch Gen Psychiatry [Internet]. 1999 May 1 [cited 2013 Oct 4];56(5):431–7. Available from: http://dx.doi.org/10.1001/archpsyc.56.5.431</ref><ref>Liebowitz MR, Quitkin FM, Stewart JW, et al. Phenelzine v imipramine in atypical depression: A preliminary report. Arch Gen Psychiatry [Internet]. 1984 Jul 1 [cited 2013 Oct 4];41(7):669–77. Available from: http://dx.doi.org/10.1001/archpsyc.1984.01790180039005</ref>及带有[[焦虑情绪|焦虑情绪]]的抑郁障碍和抑郁性[[暴食症|暴食症]]<ref>Walsh B, Stewart JW, Roose SP, Gladis M, Glassman AH. Treatment of bulimia with phenelzine: A double-blind, placebo-controlled study. Arch Gen Psychiatry [Internet]. 1984 Nov 1 [cited 2013 Oct 4];41(11):1105–9. Available from: http://dx.doi.org/10.1001/archpsyc.1983.01790220095015</ref><ref>Rothschild R, Quitkin HM, Quitkin FM, Stewart JW, Ocepek-Welikson K, McGrath PJ, et al. A double-blind placebo-controlled comparison of phenelzine and imipramine in the treatment of bulimia in atypical depressives. International Journal of Eating Disorders [Internet]. 1994 [cited 2013 Oct 4];15(1):1–9. Available from: http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/1098-108X(199401)15:1{{dead link|date=2018年5月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}<1::AID-EAT2260150102>3.0.CO;2-E/abstract</ref><ref>Walsh BT, Stewart JW, Roose SP, Gladis M, Glassman AH. A double-blind trial of phenelzine in bulimia. Journal of Psychiatric Research [Internet]. 1985 [cited 2013 Oct 4];19(2–3):485–9. Available from: http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022395685900585 {{Wayback|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022395685900585 |date=20181211080133 }}</ref><ref>Walsh B, Gladis M, Roose SP, Stewart JW, Stetner F, Glassman AH. Phenelzine vs placebo in 50 patients with bulimia. Arch Gen Psychiatry [Internet]. 1988 May 1 [cited 2013 Oct 4];45(5):471–5. Available from: http://dx.doi.org/10.1001/archpsyc.1988.01800290091011</ref>以及[[創傷後心理壓力緊張症候群|創傷後心理壓力緊張症候群]]<ref>Davidson J, Ingram J, Kilts C. A pilot study of phenelzine in the treatment of post-traumatic stress disorder. The British Journal of Psychiatry. 1987;150:252–5.</ref>和[[边缘型人格障碍|边缘型人格障碍]]的治疗有效。<ref>Soloff PH, Cornelius J, George A, Nathan S, Perel JM, Ulrich RF. Efficacy of phenelzine and haloperidol in borderline personality disorder. Arch Gen Psychiatry [Internet]. 1993 May 1 [cited 2013 Oct 4];50(5):377–85. Available from: http://dx.doi.org/10.1001/archpsyc.1993.01820170055007</ref>根据最近的回顾性分析，MAOIs在对[[双向障碍|双向障碍]]病情控制中也显现出有效性。<ref>Mallinger AG, Frank E, Thase ME, Barwell MM, DiazGranados N, Luckenbaugh DA, et al. Revisiting the Effectiveness of Standard Antidepressants in Bipolar Disorder: Are Monoamine Oxidase Inhibitors Superior? Psychopharmacol Bull [Internet]. 2009 [cited 2013 Oct 4];42(2):64–74. Available from: http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3570273/ {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3570273/ |date=20210611140421 }}</ref>也有报道显示MAOIs对[[强迫症|强迫症]]、[[拔毛癖|拔毛癖]]、[[畸形恐惧|畸形恐惧]]以及[[回避型人格障碍|回避型人格障碍]]的治疗有效，但这些报告都来自不受控制的病例情况下的分析。<ref name="pmid2248064">{{cite journal |author=Liebowitz MR, Hollander E, Schneier F, ''et al.'' |title=Reversible and irreversible monoamine oxidase inhibitors in other psychiatric disorders |journal=Acta Psychiatr Scand Suppl |volume=360 |issue= |pages=29–34 |year=1990 |pmid=2248064 |doi=10.1111/j.1600-0447.1990.tb05321.x }}</ref>

MAOIs也可选择性抑制B型单胺氧化酶（由此影响[[多巴胺能神经元|多巴胺能神经元]]），从而用于帕金森氏病的治疗，同时还是一种[[预防|预防]][[偏头痛|偏头痛]]的方法。抑制A型单胺氧化酶和B型单胺氧化酶的MAOIs则用于治疗临床抑郁症以及焦虑症。

MAOIs專門用于治疗带有惊恐障碍或癔病样心境苦闷(hysteroid dysphoria)的疑似患者，及长期有抑郁情绪的门诊患者。<ref>http://www.psycom.net/hysteroid.html {{Wayback|url=http://www.psycom.net/hysteroid.html |date=20160306110637 }} {{cite journal |year=1987 |last1=Dowson |first1=JH |title=MAO inhibitors in mental disease: their current status. [Review] |volume=23 |pages=121–38 |journal=Journal of Neural Transmission. Supplementum |pmid=3295114}}</ref>

==药物机理==
MAOIs通过抑制[[单胺氧化酶|单胺氧化酶]]的活性来发挥作用，由此来减缓[[单胺类递质|单胺类递质]]的分解以加强递质的作用。单胺氧化酶有两种异构体，A型单胺氧化酶(MAO-A)，B型单胺氧化酶(MAO-B)。MAO-A优先脱去[[5-羟色胺|5-羟色胺]]、[[N-乙酰-5-甲氧基色胺|N-乙酰-5-甲氧基色胺]]、[[肾上腺素|肾上腺素]]及[[去甲肾上腺素|去甲肾上腺素]]的氨基；而MAO-B则优先脱去[[苯基乙胺|苯基乙胺]]及[[痕量胺|痕量胺]]的氨基。两者对[[多巴胺|多巴胺]]的脱氨基作用相同。

===可逆性===
早期的MAOIs与单胺氧化酶共价结合，因此这种抑制效果是不可逆的。被MAOI以[[共价键|共价键]]结合的酶会永久失去活性，除非细胞合成新的酶替代它。这些酶大约每14天更新一次。一些如[[吗氯贝胺|吗氯贝胺]]的新型MAOIs是可逆的，它们能脱离被抑制的酶，并使酶正常促进底物的[[分解代谢|分解代谢]]。这种方式的抑制的程度取决于单胺氧化酶及MAOI的浓度。

在[[骆驼蓬|骆驼蓬]]、[[死藤水|死藤水]]、[[死藤水藤|死藤水藤]]以及[[西番莲|西番莲]]中发现的[[骆驼蓬碱|骆驼蓬碱]]是一种可逆的A型单胺氧化酶抑制剂(RIMA)<ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=2c2K-epbCDQC&pg=PA237&lpg=PA237&dq=harmaline+antidepressant&source=web&ots=IrcpVr4R_H&sig=5FvlysKKEN7Hb4_YjfgoZM8rsTg Edward J. Massaro, Handbook of Neurotoxicology]</ref>

===选择性===
除可逆性外，大多MAOIs还对单胺氧化酶有选择性。一些MAOIs同等程度地抑制MAO-A和MAO-B，而另一些则能更强地抑制其中的一种。

对MAO-A的抑制主要能减缓5-羟色胺、去甲肾上腺素和多巴胺的分解。选择性抑制MAO-A则能迫使[[酪胺|酪胺]]通过MAO-B代谢。<ref name="pmid9432289">{{cite journal |author=Nowakowska E, Chodera A |title=[Inhibitory monoamine oxidases of the new generation] |language=pl |journal=Pol. Merkur. Lekarski |volume=3 |issue=13 |pages=1–4 |date=July 1997 |pmid=9432289 }}</ref>如果与其他类型的5-羟色胺增强剂联用，其相互作用可能导致5-羟色胺综合征，严重时可能威胁生命，而与非选择性及非可逆的旧型MAOIs联用也可能造成此后果。特别地，旧型MAOIs还有可能与富含酪胺的食物产生相互作用。酪胺能在MAO-A或MAO-B的作用下分解，而对两种酶的抑用可能导致酪胺难以分解而过多堆积，因此，用药时对酪胺的摄入必须予以控制。

对MAO-B的抑制主要能减少多巴胺及苯乙胺的分解，用药时没有相关的饮食限制。MAO-B也能促进酪胺的代谢，而多巴胺、苯乙胺、酪胺三者之间唯一不同的在于两个位于碳3和碳4位的酚基。在酪胺中，碳4位的羟基不与MAO-B产生[[位阻|位阻]]。<ref>[http://www.sciencedirect.com/science?_ob=ArticleURL&_udi=B6WB5-4NVJYMH-2&_user=521319&_coverDate=08%2F15%2F2007&_rdoc=1&_fmt=high&_orig=search&_origin=search&_sort=d&_docanchor=&view=c&_acct=C000026018&_version=1&_urlVersion=0&_userid=521319&md5=4cce208ef76638c64e8ce59bf3a3ab13&searchtype=a ScienceDirect - Archives of Biochemistry and Biophysics : Structural insights into the mechanism of amine oxidation by monoamine oxidases A and B<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>[[丙炔苯丙胺|丙炔苯丙胺]]和[[雷沙吉兰|雷沙吉兰]]两种MAO-B抑制剂，已经过FDA认证不需要限制饮食，除非高剂量使用（这会导致选择性失去）<ref name="Emsam"/><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.elitenetpharmacy.com/pd_azilect.cfm | title = Rasagiline: a neuroprotective smart drug? | accessdate = 2007-12-02 | author = [[BLTC_Research|BLTC Research]] [http://www.bltc.com/] | year = 2006 | work = The Good Drug Guide | quote = At dosages above around 2 mg per day, rasagiline loses its selectivity for MAO type B and also inhibits MAO type A. An MAO-B selective regimen does not cause significant tyramine [[potentiation|potentiation]], the dreaded '[[cheese_effect|cheese effect]]' common to users of older unselective and irreversible MAOIs who eat tyramine-rich foods. This will be taken with and without food.  Thus, low-dosage rasagiline demands no special dietary restrictions. | archive-date = 2007-12-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20071209030605/http://www.elitenetpharmacy.com/pd_azilect.cfm | dead-url = no }}</ref>

==风险性==
口服MAOIs会减缓饮食胺的分解。富含酪胺的食物经消化吸收，人体可能会面临[[高血压危象|高血压危象]]。<ref name="Stah"/>药物起效的剂量因人而异，有时剂量差别会很大，不同MAOIs的抑制效果和选择性的差异也会影响药物的用量。{{Citation needed|date=December 2013}}

酪胺导致高血压反应的具体机理尚不清楚，有假说认为酪胺取代了囊泡中储存的去甲肾上腺素。<ref>{{cite journal | last = Jacob | first = Giris | coauthors = Gamboa, Alfredo; Diedrich, André; Shibao, Cyndya; Robertson, David; Biaggioni, Italo | date = August 2005 | title = Tyramine-Induced Vasodilation Mediated by Dopamine Contamination: A Paradox Resolved | journal = Hypertension | volume = 46 | issue = 2 | publisher = Lippincott Williams & Wilkins | doi = 10.1161/01.HYP.0000172353.62657.8b | url = http://pt.wkhealth.com/pt/re/hyper/pdfhandler.00004268-200508000-00023.pdf | accessdate = 2007-12-02 | quote = Tyramine displaces norepinephrine from neuronal vesicles into the axoplasm, and it is likely that some of it is converted to DHPG, and only a portion reaches the circulation. | pmid = 15967868 | pages = 355–9 }}{{Dead link|date=2019年12月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>这可能会引发突触释放过量去甲肾上腺素，从而导致高血压危象。另一种理论则认为是[[儿茶酚胺|儿茶酚胺]]的过量堆积导致了高血压危象。<ref>A.J Giannini. Psychotropic Drug Overdose. In  M.E. Keshavan,J.S. Jennedy. (eds) Drug-Induced Dysfunction in Psychiatry. NY, Hemisphere Publishing,1992, pg. 41. ISBN 0-89116-961-X</ref>

[[酪氨酸|酪氨酸]]是酪胺的前体，后者是前者的分解的产物。在消化道中的发酵作用下，酪氨酸能脱羟基变为酪胺。而通常酪胺会在肝脏中脱氨基变为无活性的代谢产物，但是当肝单胺氧化酶（主要是MAO-A）被抑制时，肝脏就难以清理通过它的酪胺，这时血液中的酪胺水平就会攀升。高浓度的酪胺会与酪氨酸竞争通过血脑屏障（由芳香族氨基酸协助运输），这些物质将进入肾上腺素能神经末梢。一旦进入细胞质，酪胺就通过[[小泡单胺类转运体|小泡单胺类转运体]]（VMAT）被运送到突触小泡，由此替换去甲肾上腺素。去甲肾上腺素大量地从小泡释放到细胞间质会积累高血压危象的可能。不经治疗，高血压危象可能引发中风或心律失常。总的来说，目前可逆的A型单胺氧化酶抑制剂还没有这种风险。而两种肠单胺氧化酶抑制都能导致[[发烧|发烧]]、[[恶心|恶心]]，如果在食物中摄入大量左旋多巴，还能导致精神症状。

可能含有较高水平酪胺（包括肝代谢及发酵产物）的食物如酒精饮料和熟奶酪。<ref name=Mosher>Mosher, Clayton James, and Scott Akins. Drugs and Drug Policy : The Control of Consciousness Alteration. Thousand Oaks, Calif.: Sage, 2007.</ref>含有左旋多巴的如蚕豆。但这些饮食限制在选择性B型单胺氧化酶抑制剂使用者并不必要，除非药物剂量较高。

值得一提的是，一些肉汁、酵母膏含有特别高水平的酪胺，它们不应与在用药期间食用。

MAOIs被首次引入时，这些风险还并不清楚，以至于在40年中有接近100人死于高血压危象。{{Citation needed|date=December 2007}}大概由于该药出现的突发的严重不良反应，MAOIs被认为相当危险，致使其曾一度在美国完全下架。现在认为MAOIs是一种用于中长期治疗的一种可行选择，惟须遵循精神科医生的指导。

MAOIs使用中最显著的风险就是与非处方药和处方药、违法药品及一些保健补充剂（如色氨酸）之间潜在的相互作用。对医务人员的相关药品的回避提示至关重要。因此，不少使用MAOIs治疗的患者随身携带一张“MAOI卡”，以使急救人员知道应避免哪些药品。（例如肾上腺素剂量应减少75%。）<ref name=Mosher />MAOI使用者中发生因药物相互作用或饮食不当造成不良反应的危险特别高，因为这些患者常常是“不在乎自己的生死”的抑郁症患者。<ref>Kramer, Peter D. Listening to Prozac. New York, N.Y., U.S.A.: Viking, 1993.</ref>

[[色氨酸|色氨酸]]补充剂不应与MAOIs共用，因为这可能会导致5-羟色胺综合征，严重时可能致命。<ref name="Boyer-NEJM">{{cite journal |last=Boyer |first=EW |authorlink= |last2=Shannon |first2=M |authorlink2=Michael Shannon (pediatrician) |title=The serotonin syndrome |url=http://toxicology.ucsd.edu/art%203%20serotonin%20syndrome.pdf |journal=N Engl J Med |volume=352 |issue=11 |pages=1112–20 |year=2005 |pmid=15784664 |doi=10.1056/NEJMra041867 |access-date=2014-03-26 |archive-date=2013-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130618053344/http://toxicology.ucsd.edu/art%203%20serotonin%20syndrome.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>

除非有专业监护，MAOIs不应与其他精神药物（抗抑郁药、止痛药、兴奋剂等，不论合法与非法）共用。某些特定药物联用可能导致死亡，常见的包括与[[选择性5-羟色胺再摄取抑制剂|选择性5-羟色胺再摄取抑制剂]]、[[三环类抗抑郁药|三环类抗抑郁药]]、[[亚甲二氧甲基苯丙胺|亚甲二氧甲基苯丙胺]]、[[哌替啶|哌替啶]]<ref>Pharmacology from H.P. Rang, M.M. Dale, J.M. Ritter, P.K. Moore, year 2003, chapter 38</ref>、[[反胺苯环醇|反胺苯环醇]]以及[[右美沙芬|右美沙芬]]的联用。{{Citation needed|date=January 2009}}因MAOIs的增强作用和延长效应，在使用肾上腺素、去甲肾上腺素或多巴胺时必须将剂量降到很低。

尼古丁单独使用被显示出“相对较弱”的上瘾性<ref name="pmid16177026">{{cite journal |author=Guillem K, Vouillac C, Azar MR, ''et al.'' |title=Monoamine oxidase inhibition dramatically increases the motivation to self-administer nicotine in rats |journal=J. Neurosci. |volume=25 |issue=38 |pages=8593–600 |date=September 2005 |pmid=16177026 |doi=10.1523/JNEUROSCI.2139-05.2005 |url=}}</ref>而在对鼠的实验中，与MAOI共用时，鼠的感受性显著提升，显示出潜在的上瘾性提升。<ref name="pmid14592678">{{cite journal |author=Villégier AS, Blanc G, Glowinski J, Tassin JP |title=Transient behavioral sensitization to nicotine becomes long-lasting with monoamine oxidases inhibitors |journal=Pharmacol. Biochem. Behav. |volume=76 |issue=2 |pages=267–74 |date=September 2003 |pmid=14592678 |doi= 10.1016/S0091-3057(03)00223-5|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_pharmacology-biochemistry-and-behavior_2003-09_76_2/page/267}}</ref><ref name="pmid16884739">{{cite journal|title=Contribution of monoamine oxidase (MAO) inhibition to tobacco and alcohol addiction|pages=1969–1973|issn=0024-3205|journal=Life Sciences|volume=79|issue=21|date=2006-10-19|doi=10.1016/j.lfs.2006.06.010|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16884739|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=Jan van Amsterdam, Reinskje Talhout, Wim Vleeming, Antoon Opperhuizen|pmid=16884739|archive-date=2018-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180916020900/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16884739|dead-url=no}}</ref>这也许体现出戒烟的困难，因为烟草中除尼古丁外还含有天然的单胺氧化酶抑制化合物。<ref name="pmid11343627">{{cite journal|title=Monoamine oxidases and tobacco smoking|pages=33–42|issn=1461-1457|journal=The International Journal of Neuropsychopharmacology|volume=4|issue=1|date=2001-3|doi=10.1017/S1461145701002188|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11343627|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=I. Berlin, R. M. Anthenelli|pmid=11343627|archive-date=2019-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728213611/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11343627|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="pmid8943061">{{cite journal|title=Brain monoam